[h2 id=VisionForAnUpdatedSite 
	"Vision for an updated site
	$LF
]h2
[hr 
]hr
[div class=p 
	"Just to have documentation for it. I would like TASvideos site to be easy to use both for people making TASes as well as viewers, and I believe the best way to do that is to make game specific pages more prominent. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=We have a database for game pages already|href=/Games)
	". It's auto generated and woefully underused. It's also incredibly difficult to find unless you know it's there. First priority would be to make links to these pages more prominent. Second would be to repurpose those pages so that all information anyone might need can be found there.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I would like game pages to include:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" General game information
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" List of publications (with obsoletion history chain)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" List of submissions
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" WIPs/userfiles (with the ability to embed streaming videos)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Information on known tricks and glitches.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Information of version differences with links to different versions of the same game if applicable (i.e. on different consoles).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" A mirror of the forum thread dedicated to that game, which users can write replies to from the game page. 
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Basically just making sure all information you might ever need on a game is consolidated in one place rather than forcing users to go to different areas of the site to try to piece things together. 
]div
